name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Mind Stone
info.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Mind Stone: Draw a card.
info.flavor_text: During biotransference, the Necrontyr lost almost all individuality. What little remained was imprisoned within a living metal form.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Mask of Memory
info.oracle_text:
Whenever equipped creature deals combat damage to a player, you may draw two cards. If you do, discard a card.
Equip {1} ({1}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

info.name: Lychguard
info.oracle_text: Guardian Protocols — {3}{B}, Sacrifice Lychguard: Return all legendary creature cards from your graveyard to your hand.
info.flavor_text:
"Only the deathless can truly comprehend the burden of unfailing loyalty."
—Vargard Obyron of the Sautekh Dynasty

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Lokhust Heavy Destroyer
info.oracle_text:
Flying

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Living Death
info.oracle_text: Each player exiles all creature cards from their graveyard, then sacrifices all creatures they control, then puts all cards they exiled this way onto the battlefield.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Illuminor Szeras
info.oracle_text: Secrets of the Soul — {T}, Sacrifice another creature: Add an amount of {B} equal to the sacrificed creature's mana value.
info.flavor_text: "Immortality is not quite the same as invulnerability, but it is close enough."

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Hexmark Destroyer
info.oracle_text:
Multi-threat Eliminator — Hexmark Destroyer can't be blocked except by six or more creatures.
Unearth {4}{B}{B} ({4}{B}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Hedron Archive
info.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}{C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Hedron Archive: Draw two cards.
info.flavor_text: The vaults of the Necron Dynasties contain all manner of esoteric artifacts, most forged long before many of the younger races even existed.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Go for the Throat
info.oracle_text: Destroy target nonartifact creature.
info.flavor_text:
"Pray that night is upon us, for if this twilight is the work of the Necrons, we are all dead men."
—Address by Lieutenant Krakow prior to the Bloodmoon Massacres

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Ghost Ark
info.oracle_text:
Flying
Repair Barge — Whenever Ghost Ark becomes crewed, each artifact creature card in your graveyard gains unearth {3} until end of turn.
Crew 2 (Tap any number of creatures you control with total power 2 or more: This Vehicle becomes an artifact creature until end of turn.)

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Gilded Lotus
info.oracle_text: {T}: Add three mana of any one color.
info.flavor_text:
"The ancient Necron race has achieved this pinnacle of elegance through their relentless pursuit of utility."
—Tech-Priest Darvin, executed for heresy 1256998.M41

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Endless Atlas
info.oracle_text: {2}, {T}: Draw a card. Activate only if you control three or more lands with the same name.
info.flavor_text:
"While we slept, our inferiors infested the worlds that belong to us. Now, we awaken once more."
—Szarekh, the Silent King

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Dread Return
info.oracle_text:
Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
Flashback—Sacrifice three creatures. (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)
info.flavor_text:
"Bolters, flamers, plasma—we hit the xenos with everything, and it just kept coming."
—Captain Uriel Ventris

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Desert of the Glorified
info.oracle_text:
Desert of the Glorified enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {1}{B} ({1}{B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
info.flavor_text: On countless frontier worlds, below silica sand, blasted chalk, or bubbling marsh, slumbering Necrons await.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Defile
info.oracle_text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn for each Swamp you control.
info.flavor_text:
"Agresto, bring up the rear . . . Agresto?"
—Sergeant Dremark Eigen, last words

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Darkness
info.oracle_text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.
info.flavor_text: By the physical laws of the universe, darkness is merely the absence of light. Necrons can harness the power of other dimensions, where darkness is tangible and moldable.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Cryptek
info.oracle_text: {1}{B}, {T}: Choose another target artifact creature you control. When that creature dies this turn, return it to the battlefield tapped under your control.
info.flavor_text: There are those who draw false comparisons between the tech-magi of the Adeptus Mechanicus and the xenotechnologists of the necron race. There can be no mercy for such heretics.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Cryptothrall
info.oracle_text: Protector — Other artifact creatures you control have hexproof.
info.flavor_text: Bound to a cryptek, the cryptothrall exists for one reason: to defend its master to the death.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Cranial Plating
info.flavor_text: The flesh of the Necrontyr is a memory so distant as to be nearly mythical.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Convergence of Dominion
info.oracle_text:
Dynastic Command Node — As long as you control your commander, activated abilities of cards in your graveyard cost {2} less to activate. This effect can't reduce the mana in that ability's activation cost to less than one mana.
Translocation Protocols — {3}, {T}: Mill three cards.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Commander's Sphere
info.oracle_text:
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
Sacrifice Commander's Sphere: Draw a card.
info.flavor_text: Within it rests the power of a sun, and none of the warmth.

Unearth {2}{B} ({2}{B}: Return this card from your graveyard to the battlefield. It gains haste. Exile it at the beginning of the next end step or if it would leave the battlefield. Unearth only as a sorcery.)

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)

info.oracle_text: Put target artifact or creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. Shuffle Beacon of Unrest into its owner's library.

{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {B} ({B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
info.flavor_text: Millennia of constant warfare have left many planets with very little worth fighting over.

info.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
info.flavor_text: All Necrons bear the mark of the Triarch, a brand upon their living-metal skin that binds them to their dynasty.

info.flavor_text: "You mortals turn to dust in the blink of an eye. I only expedite your fate."

info.name: Necron Deathmark

Flying

Polluted Mire enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
info.flavor_text: As the continent sank over the course of eons, the tomb complex slowly flooded. The sleeping Necrons, their stasis crypts corrupted, never awoke.

info.name: Reliquary Tower
info.oracle_text:
You have no maximum hand size.
{T}: Add {C}.
info.flavor_text:
"Let the others bicker over their little worlds and stars. I have an empire of knowledge, and it encompasses all others."
—Trazyn the Infinite

info.name: Sautekh Immortal

Flash

info.flavor_text:
"Nothing clears a battlefield like a Deathstrike missile. Wait. Is something moving out there?"
—Commmander Zander At'lan, Tallarn 115th Armoured Regiment

info.name: Sceptre of Eternal Glory

{T}: Add one mana of any color.
{T}: Add three mana of any one color. Activate only if you control three or more lands with the same name.

info.name: Shard of the Nightbringer

Flying

info.flavor_text:
"Aza'gorod, the Nightbringer. The embodiment of death. A killer of stars and of worlds."
—Illuminor Szeras

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Skorpekh Destroyer
info.oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Hyperphase Threshers — Whenever an artifact you control enters, Skorpekh Destroyer gains first strike until end of turn.
info.flavor_text: Nothing can override the hard-wired desire to kill that empowers these rage-driven Necrons.

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)
info.name: Sol Ring
info.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.

"Once, the C'tan sought to rule us. Now it is they who serve us, their shards powering our great machines."

name: Necron Dynasties (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)

info.flavor_text:
"When the Silent King saw what had been done, he knew at last the true nature of the C'tan, and the doom they had wrought in his name."
—*The Book of Mournful Night*
